Package ohos.net.http

Class SslError

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.net.http.SslError

  • public class SslError
extends Object
    Represents a set of Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) errors associated with X.509 authentication.

    This class provides methods for performing operations on SSL errors, such as adding and querying errors. SSL errors are stored by bit, and so multiple SSL errors can be added.

    Since:
    4

      • addError

        public boolean addError​(int error)
        Adds a specified SSL error to this SslError object.
        Parameters:
        error - Indicates the SSL error to add.
          The following error types are supported:
        • SSL_CERT_NOT_YET_VALID
        • SSL_CERT_EXPIRED
        • SSL_CERT_NAME_INVALID
        • SSL_CERT_AUTHORITY_INVALID
        • SSL_CERT_DATE_INVALID
        • SSL_CERT_INVALID
        Returns:
        Returns true if the SSL error is added; returns false otherwise.
